cards.title: 108 Gracious Gifts
cards.text: While you have equal or less ghost rock than each other player, you may discard an extra card at Nightfall. Noon, Pay 2 Ghost Rock, Boot:Unboot your dude.

cards.title: House of Many Faiths
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Shuffle a card from your hand and a card from your discard pile into your deck. Your dude with a Miracle moves to town square, unboots, and gets +1 Influence.

cards.title: Farnum's Consortium
cards.text: In-town deeds you own with one or more of your dudes present get +1 production. Noon, boot: If you have fewer cards in hand than each opponent, pay 2 ghost rock to draw a card.

cards.title: Morgan Regulators
cards.text: If it is Sundown and there has not been a shootout this turn, each player's influence total at each location is limited to 5. Noon, Boot: Move your dude to the town square. If they have a Horse, unboot them.

cards.title: Encroaching Darkness
cards.text: Reduce the cost of the first Abomination you play from your hand each turn by 1. Noon, Boot: Boot your dude to target an opposing dude in their location with lower value. Reduce the target's influence by 1. If your dude is an Abomination, reduce the target's bullet rating by 1.

cards.title: Serpentine Syndicate
cards.text: React, Boot: After your dude successfully casts a spell while not at home, you may discard a card from your hand to gain 1 ghost rock and draw 1 card.

cards.title: Black Hills Guardians
cards.text: Dudes may not refuse your call outs at Holy Grounds. Shootout Repeat: Boot a Holy Ground you control to move one of your dudes there into your posse.

cards.title: The Spiritual Society
cards.text: If you have the most or are tied for the most influence in town square at Nightfall, draw a card. Noon, Boot: Boot your dude to boot an opposing dude with less influence at the same location.

cards.title: Law Dogs
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Boot your dudes with total influence greater than target dude's influence to add 1 bounty to that dude.

cards.title: Saved By Grace
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Target your skilled dude that is not at home to make a skill check against a difficulty of 7. If successful, boot your dude to look at the top five cards of your deck plus your dude's Blessed rating. You may discard a card from your hand to add one of those cards to your hand. Shuffle your deck. Gain 1 ghost rock.

cards.title: Deadwood Miner's Alliance
cards.text: Your dudes with 4 or more bounty are worth +1 control points while in the town square. Noon, Boot: Boot your dude at a location you do not own. If the location is Public, give them 2 bounty and gain 1 ghost rock. If the location is Private, give them 1 bounty and gain 2 ghost rock.

cards.title: The Sloane Gang
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Boot your dude in the town square. If that dude is still in the town square at Nightfall, either gain 1 ghost rock per other player, or give that dude 1 permanent control point if they do no already have a control point.

cards.title: Daomei Wang
cards.text: React: After Daomei enters play during High Noon, move one of your other dudes (without booting).
cards.flavor: "I need you Righteous Bandits to find out who's doing Farnum's dirty work." - Huang Li

cards.title: Randall
cards.text: While you have dudes at three or more different in-town locations, your maximum hand size is increased by one.
cards.flavor: "Now go forth and spread the legend of The People's Bandit! Inspire the townsfolk, so that they might know: they are not forgotten."

cards.title: Asakichi Cooke
cards.text: Noon: Discard a card to move one of your other dudes from this location (without booting, even if booted).
cards.flavor: "My daughter learned her trade in Gomorra. Tombstone will be a walk in the park." - Forster Cooke

cards.title: Natalya
cards.text: At the start of the Production phase, if you have less ghost rock in your stash than each other player and Natalya is at a deed, you gain the production of the deed this turn and other players do not.

cards.title: Xui Yin Chen
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: All dudes in Xui Yin Chen's posse become studs and get +1 influence.
cards.flavor: "Sadly, it was only upon her death that her brother finally took things seriously." -He Fang

cards.title: Shi Long Peng
cards.flavor: "I see now why it's said he has the strength of a wrathful bodhisattva. He truly seems prepared to stand before demons and protect the townsfolk." - Hao-T'e Zui

cards.title: Emre, The Turkish Bear (Exp.1)
cards.text: Repeat React: After Emre successfully performs a Technique during a shootout, draw a card and give Emre +1 bullets. You may use this ability once per shootout.

cards.title: Yunxu Jiang
cards.text: While Yunxu Jiang is in a shootout at a location you control, each of your other dudes in the posse gets +1 bullets and +1 value.
cards.flavor: "You will not harm these people."

cards.title: Forster Cooke
cards.text: While Forster is at a Saloon or Casino, your other dudes get +1 bullets and +1 value.
cards.flavor: "We do our best to assist the Twilight Legion after what happened to Mr. Jackson. A drink for those who fight against the terrors in the world"

cards.title: He Fang
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Play a non-Gadget Abomination from your hand at this location, reducing its cost by 2.
cards.flavor: "Ghost miners? Perhaps we can release these troubled souls, and guide them toward rebirth."

cards.title: Jim Hexter
cards.text: Shootout Repeat: Pay 1 ghost rock to the controller of the opposing posse's leader or mark to make Jim a stud. You may use this ability once per shootout.
cards.flavor: "We'll need to bribe people for more information. So we'll need to steal from them first to afford it."

cards.title: Stevie Lyndon
cards.text: While casting Hymns, Stevie gets +4 Blessed skill.
cards.flavor: "I've heard some fools say he's so talented he must have sold his soul to the Devil, but out Lord works through his music." - Padre Ernesto de Diaz

cards.title: Hao-T'e Zui, The Mad Monk
cards.text: If you are , reduce the cost to play Hao-T'e Zui by the number of different locations with at least one of your dudes. Shootout, Boot: Discard an opposing goods.

cards.title: Irving Patterson
cards.text: When Irving joins a posse, gain 1 ghost rock.
cards.flavor: "Sometimes I think that even I could run this company better than Miss Lula. She burns through our coffers faster than a bullet."

cards.title: Arnold Stewart
cards.text: Noon: Boot Arnold's Gadget to discard the top five cards of your deck. If one of those cards was an Out of Town deed, you may boot Arnold to put that card in your hand.

cards.title: Chuan "Jen" Qí
cards.text:
While Jen has a Horse, she gets +1 Influence.
While Jen has a Gadget, she gets +2 Bullets.
cards.flavor: "The fight against Stone feels neverending"

cards.title: Seamus O'Toole
cards.text: Shootout: Target your dude with a Weapon Gadget in this shootout. Pull. If the pull is a club, reduce that dude to a zero draw. Otherwise, that Gadget gets +2 bullets.

cards.title: Diego Linares
cards.text: While inventing a Horse or Sidekick, Diego gets +4 Mad Scientist.
cards.flavor: "A master of his craft, but I think getting the barnyard smell right is a step too far." -Arnold Stewart

cards.title: Nathan Shane
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: Look at a number of random cards in an opponent's hand up to Nathan's Bullets. You may discard one revealed action card.
cards.flavor: "I've avenged both Graves and Wiles, but there's still plenty of outlaws to put in the dirt."

cards.title: Jon Longstride
cards.text: Boot: Unboot Jon's Horse. You may use an ability of the Horse an additional time this turn.
cards.flavor: "I've never met a man more at home in the saddle than him."

cards.title: Lane Healey
cards.text: While Lane has a Horse, he gets +2 bullets and -1 upkeep.
cards.flavor: "Next time I see that rat Jonah Essex, I'm gonna use the 'shoot first, talk later' approach."

cards.title: Jarrett Blake
cards.text: Shootout: If Jarrett has a Horse, swap him with one of your dudes in the posse (Jarrett moves to the shootout's location and joins the posse. The other dude moves to Jarrett's original location and leaves the posse).

cards.title: Maggie Harris
cards.text: Noon Job, Boot: Mark another in-town location. If successful, attach a Horse from your discard to any of your dudes, reducing its cost by 1 (a Gadget still needs to be invented.)
cards.flavor: "Still wranglin' out in the Maze somewhere. I miss her every day." - Jarrett Blake

cards.title: Buckin' Billy Ballard
cards.text: While Billy has a Horse, he gets +1 bullets and +1 influence. Noon/Shootout: Boot Billy's Horse to draw a card. You may boot a dude at this location.
cards.flavor: "Swear he'll hurt his steed in a stunt, but he hasn't yet." - Irving Patterson

cards.title: POST-A-TRON
cards.text: You can include POST-A-TRON in your starting gang.If you do, you must boot a Mad Scientist, who make a skill check of difficulty 6. If you fail, or cannot make, the skill check, discard POST-A-TRON. Noon, Boot: if POST-A-TRON is at the town square, gain 3 ghost rock.

cards.title: E.B. Farnum
cards.text: If you are , you may boot any number of your dudes to reduce the cost to play Farnum by the total influence of the dudes booted. Noon: Give a dude at this location -1 influence.
cards.flavor: "We built this town from nothing. No one will take it from us."

cards.title: Landon Grimes
cards.text: Shootout: Your Abomination or Huckster joins Landon's posse.
cards.flavor: "Folks gone missing? Sorry, Deputy, I ain't seen or heard a thing"

cards.title: Pagliaccio
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: One opposing dude gets -1 bullets and -1 value.
cards.flavor: "We are free of our strings and happy to serve in your new circus, Ms. Cline."

cards.title: Mongwau The Mighty
cards.text: Shootout: Discard a Hex from Mongwau to make him a stud.
cards.flavor: "Roll up, roll up and see the magical maneuvers of the mighty Mongwau of the Serpentine!... you ghost rock grubbing morons."

cards.title: The Brute
cards.text: When you ace The Brute to cover casualties in a shootout, reduce your remaining casualties by 2.
cards.flavor: "You'd think all that tearing would deter him from flexing so much, but it just fuels his act. The crowds love it." -Avie Cline

cards.title: Valeria Batten
cards.text: Valeria can invent Mystical Gadgets using her Huckster skill (as if it were Mad Scientist).
cards.flavor: "In hindsight, I should have been suspicious of a circus that required my talents."

cards.title: Alfred Byrne
cards.text: Noon: Boot Alfred or one of his attached Hexes to boot an attachment at this location.
cards.flavor: "Excellent! If they're expendable, then we've plenty of blood for the ritual."

cards.title: Bobo
cards.text: Bobo gets a bullet bonus equal to the highest Huckster skill rating in play.
cards.flavor: "May he rot in the hell he surely came from." -Nathan Shane

cards.title: Alan Campbell
cards.text: Noon: Call out a 0-influence dude at this location.
cards.flavor: "Tarnation, ain't no such thing as werewolves. Besides, if'n there were, it ain't gonna be called Alan." -Jimmy Suggs, final words

cards.title: Sylvester Heath
cards.text: Noon: Boot Sylvester's attached Hex or Mystical goods to move to an in-town location.
cards.flavor: "In my shop we've even got the very cards Wild Bill was holding when he died. Sure you don't wanna stop in?"

cards.title: Avie Cline
cards.flavor: "With Hawley and Adler vanquished, The Fourth Ring folded. I struck like a snake in the grass, my patience finally rewarded. This is my show now, The Serpentine Syndicate!"

cards.title: Kevin Wainwright
cards.text: Noon: Move Kevin to a location with a Huckster (without booting.) Kevin becomes a stud.
cards.flavor: "I heard Abram cut him down during his hunt for Adler. Good riddance, I never liked the little creep." -Avie Cline

cards.title: Jia Mein
cards.text: Shootout Repeat: Attach a Hex to Jia Mein (paying all costs) to make him a stud. (This ability can be used while booted, and in a location you do not control.)
cards.flavor: "Your plan for Deadwood intrigues me, Ms. Perivale."

cards.title: Ursula, The Worm Queen
cards.text: If you are , reduce the cost to play Ursula by the number of Hucksters you control. Noon: Attach a Hex from another Huckster you own to Urusula. If that Hex is booted, you may discard a card to unboot it. If you do, its actions may be used an additional time this turn.

cards.title: Alexander Sequoia
cards.text: While Alexander is in town square, you may discard an additional card at Nightfall. Noon: If Alexander is in town square, unboot Alexander.
cards.flavor: "A man of bearing and influence, whomever he stands among." -Marcia Ridge

cards.title: Mazatl
cards.text: Noon: Move Mazatl to a Totem's location.
cards.flavor: "He's a master of totems sent by the Eagle Wardens to assist with our needs." -Eagle Woman That All Look At

cards.title: Marcia Ridge
cards.text: While Marcia is at the town square and you have more influence there than each other player, you may use abilities on adjacent deeds as if you controlled them and Marcia were at that location.
cards.flavor: "She remains in Gomorra as an ambassador for the Wardens." -Black Elk

cards.title: Lydia Bear-Hands
cards.text: Resolution, Boot: Boot Lydia's Spirit to give one of your dudes Harrowed until the end of the shootout.
cards.flavor: "I have seen too much suffering at the hands of the forces of evil, but the Twilight Legion needs me to do my part."

cards.title: The Mixer
cards.text: Shootout: Target dude ignores all bullet modifiers from opponents' actions and abilities.
cards.flavor: "I seek my brothers and sisters in the Dakotas, where the Great Dance allows my people to thrive."

cards.title: Mariel Lewis
cards.text: Shootout: If you are not running a job and your posse has higher total influence than the opposing posse, remove a dude from the opposing posse and send them home (without booting).
cards.flavor: "I've faced vampires and Hawley's demons. You don't frighten me."

cards.title: Enapay
cards.text: Enapay gets +2 influence during High Noon. Noon, Boot: Another dude at this location gets +1 influence.
cards.flavor: "Rise and defend Deadwood, my brother."

cards.title: Francisco Rosales
cards.text: Noon Job, Boot: Mark the town square. If successful, attach a Sidekick or Horse from your discard pile to one of your dudes, reducing its cost by 2 (this occurs after dudes have returned home, and a Gadget still needs to be invented).
cards.flavor: "I have never met another to whom nature's flock is so attracted."

cards.title: Zachary Deloria
cards.text: While in Town Square, Zachary gets +1 Influence. If you are , Zachary has a bullet bonus equal to the highest influence among your dudes at his location (including himself).
cards.flavor: "An erstwhile friend." -Enapay

cards.title: Bloody Teeth
cards.flavor: "He's reticent about the nickname, but not even death could keep him from defending our peoples." -Alexander Sequoia

cards.title: Smiling Frog
cards.text: Noon/Shootout: Discard a card to give Smiling Frog +1 bullets. If the card was ♥, he gets +2 bullets instead.
cards.flavor: "One of these days a Maze Dragon will get at him. I just hope there'll be enough of a body left to tend to." -Lydia Bear-Hands

cards.title: Speaks-With-Earth
cards.text: React, Boot: After an opposing dude moves to this location, boot them. You may unboot a Totem at this location, and its abilities may be used an additional time this turn.

cards.title: Eagle Woman That All Look At
cards.text: If you are , reduce the cost to play Eagle Woman by the influence of one of your dudes, and she may enter play at that dude's location. Your shamans gain, "Noon/Shootout: Boot a Spirit at this location to move Eagle Woman here. If this is a shootout, she joins your posse. You may boot a dude at this location."

cards.title: Laura Banks
cards.text: Shootout: Give 1 bounty to or remove 1 bounty from a dude in this shootout.
cards.flavor: "Some new warrants for you, Mr. Bullock, and there's a US Marshall Reeves waiting in your office."

cards.title: Philip Swinford
cards.text: Whenever an opponent reveals a cheatin' hand and yours is legal, you may discard a card from your play hand to draw a card.
cards.flavor: "Gomorra tore him up and sent him to an early grave." -Clint Ramsey

cards.title: Tommy Harden
cards.text: If your opponent in Tommy's shootout reveals a cheatin' hand raise your hand rank by 1 this round. If your draw hand is also legal, raise it by 2 instead.
cards.flavor: "He couldn't catch me, but he did catch Hawley's plague." -Allie Hensman

cards.title: Padre Ernesto de Diaz
cards.text: Whenever an opponent reveals a cheatin' hand, you may boot one of Ernesto's Miracles to draw a card.
cards.flavor: "The one the newspapers call 'The Deathly Drifter' - he is not a man. Perhaps he once was, but no longer. His name is Jasper Stone."

cards.title: Andreas Andregg
cards.flavor: "He thought his fancy gadgets had a chance against the Sloane Gang until Alice ran him down. Any scientists who join the law against me will fare just as well." -Dave "Slim" Gorman

cards.title: Erik Samson
cards.text:
While Erik has a Mystical goods, he gets +1 influence.
While Erik has a melee Weapon, he is a stud.
cards.flavor: "I survived Ivor's horrors in Gomorra. God spared me to keep up the good fight."

cards.title: "Thunder Boy" Nabbe
cards.text: Shootout Repeat: If there is a wanted dude in the opposing posse, Nabbe gets a bullet bonus equal to his influence and becomes a stud. You may use this ability once per shootout.

cards.title: Drew Beauman
cards.text: Whenever an opponent reveals a cheatin' hand and yours is legal, Drew may immediately attempt to invent a Gadget without booting (other requirements of inventing must still be met.)

cards.title: Judge Harry Somerset (Exp.1)
cards.text: Noon Job, Boot: Mark a wanted dude. A 2-stud Gunslinger token enters play booted and joins your posse. If successful, discard the mark.
cards.flavor: "I find the defendant guilty as sin."

cards.title: Clyde Owens
cards.text: Noon: Clyde calls out a dude at his location. A wanted dude cannot refuse the callout.
cards.flavor: "Sheriff Burnett's fancy gizmos do a fine  job of detecting criminals, but he still needs someone like me to go and deal with them."

cards.title: Deborah West (Exp.1)
cards.text: Shootout: Boot Deborah's attached Miracle or Melee Weapon to give an opposing dude one bounty.
cards.flavor: "Don't worry, Abram. I'll carry on the good Lord's work in your name."

cards.title: Hattie DeLorre
cards.text: Shootout: Give one opposing wanted dude -3 bullets.
cards.flavor: "Murdered on the streets of Tombstone by my old gang. I'll help Deputy Dos Santos avenge here and do my best to put things right." -Maria Kingsford

cards.title: Bass Reeves
cards.text: If you are , reduce the cost to play Bass by 1 for each opposing wanted dude. If your opponent in Bass' shootout reveals a cheatin' hand and yours is legal, raise your hand rank by 1. Noon: If Bass is unbooted, cal out or boot a nearby wanted dude. If a call out is accepted by a dude at an adjacent location, boot Bass and move him to that location.

cards.title: Allie Hensman
cards.text: Noon, Boot: If Allie is at the town square, give her 1 permanent control point.
cards.flavor: "I can't believe I agreed with Jonah's plan to have me doing this stupid 'good girl' act again...

cards.title: Ike Clanton
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Give a deed Rowdy until after the next Production phase. (Control of a Rowdy deed is checked with bullets instead of influence.)
cards.flavor: "I'm lookin' for Holliday or an Earp. You find 'em, and you tell 'em they got a fight comin'!"

cards.title: Maria Kingsford
cards.text: While in a shootout, add Maria's bounty to each Huckster skill check she makes.
cards.flavor: "She used to run with the Sloane Gang. Who better than an outlaw to help us root out the last of the Cowboys?" -Elijah Clay

cards.title: Lawrence Blackwood
cards.text: Noon, Boot: If Lawrence is at a deed you do not own, give him 1 control point until he leaves that deed or the end of the turn (whichever occurs first).
cards.flavor: "He could find no peace until he met the noose." -Clyde Owens

cards.title: Miranda Clarke
cards.text:
While Miranda has a control point, she gets +1 influence.
While Miranda has at least 2 bounty, she gets +2 bullets.
cards.flavor: "With Slim in charge of the gang, Gomorra's an interesting place to be again."

cards.title: Pancho Castillo
cards.flavor: "Time to move on from Gomorroa. New town, new crew. But the same old suave caballero all the ladies are gonna be dying to know."

cards.title: "Ma" Florence Aims
cards.text: Ma's influence is equal to her bounty (maximum 4)
cards.flavor: "Boys, I need ya in Deadwood. It's time to take back yer ol' pappy's mine. Overdue we fix what those Sioux did to him."

cards.title: Baker Andrews
cards.text: Resolution: If your hand is cheatin', give Baker 1 bounty to raise your hand rank by 1.
cards.flavor: "I said, 'Get your pistol and draw a bead on him!' Not 'pastels,' ya' fool...! Ah, forget it. I can't stay mad at you, and it'll look nice on the wall." -Frank Bryant

cards.title: Dave "Slim" Gorman
cards.text: React: After Dave casts a Shootout Hex, you may discard the Hex to have all dudes currently in the shootout become a draw for this round.
cards.flavor: "I run Gomorra's streets now."

cards.title: Milt Clemons
cards.text: Whenever Milt is given bounty, gain 1 ghost rock.
cards.flavor: "Yeah, we killed him, and I'll keep on killing any bandit or red sash I come across!" - Xiong "Wendy" Cheng

cards.title: José Morales
cards.text: While in a shootout, José gains a bonus to his Huckster skill equal to his bullets.
cards.flavor: "Jonah may have surpassed him in skill, but José is still brighter and warmer than Jonah ever was or will be." - Pancho Castillo

cards.title: Larry "Sevens" Swift
cards.text: React: If Larry is in your posse after both posses are formed, boot his spell and give him 1 bounty to boot an opposing attachment. Unless you are the Dealer, Larry must be unbooted.
cards.flavor: "Give Sevens my regards,Valeria." -Maria Kingsford

cards.title: Jessica Patchett
cards.text: If you are , reduce Jessica's cost by the number of wanted dudes you control. Noon Job, Boot: Mark the opposing dude with the highest bullets (you choose in case of a tie). If successful, ace the mark.
cards.flavor: "I've moved on from that life..."

cards.title: Walter Jameson
cards.text: While Walter is at a deed owned by an opposing player, he gets +1 influence.
cards.flavor: "Maybe the Pioneer's own ace reporter can shed some light on the disappearances around here."

cards.title: Rob Wilby
cards.flavor: "I've never seen anyone else catch a bullet while wandering in town square like old Wilby. He may have accidentally stopped an assassination or two just by being in the way of the shot, and he's somehow still breathing. Not sure if he's blessed or cursed..." -Walter Jameson

cards.title: Ramiro Mendoza
cards.text: Whenever Ramiro joins a posse, pay 1 ghost rock or discard him.
cards.flavor: "'You get what you pay for' was a compliment in his case, not an insult." -Jessica Patchett

cards.title: Rattler Young 'Un
cards.text: While Rattler Young 'Un is at a deed, he uses his bullet rating to determine control of the deed instead of his influence. Shootout: If there is only one dude in the opposing posse, Rattler Young 'Un becomes a stud

cards.title: "Mahogany" Jackson
cards.text: Whenever Mahogany joins a posse, discard the top two cards of your deck.
cards.flavor: "I came back to Gomorra to put my father to rest, not to take his place."

cards.title: Wilber Crowley
cards.flavor: "Election Day was a massacre that took both mayoral candidates. Wilber didn't have the foresight to step aside. Tragic" -Nicodemus Whateley

cards.title: Roderick Byre
cards.flavor: "He could have been good for this town. But sometimes that means they can't live to see the chance." -Miranda Clarke

cards.title: El Anónimo
cards.flavor: "Don't speak much and folks will come up with the most outlandish stories to fill the silence. Some say he's a hired gun that'll go after the worst murderers out there. Me? I think he's just a cold-blooded murderer. -Laura Banks

cards.title: Ezrael Jones
cards.flavor: "Padre Ernesto de Diaz and the Order of St. George took me in, and set me on a path that's led me to saving souls in Deadwood. It should come as no surprise that shepherd could really use a gun to guard his flock around these parts."

cards.title: Angela Payne
cards.text: Noon, Boot: If Angela is at a deed you do not own, gain 2 ghost rock.
cards.flavor: "She was hired to help against Sloane back in Gomorra. I recommend her again for our current predicament." -"Mahogany" Jackson

cards.title: Clint Ramsey
cards.flavor: "I've only got one good eye, but I still shoot straighter than most folks around these parts. Here, lemme show ya."

cards.title: Nicodemus Whateley
cards.text: While your dudes are at in-town deeds, they gain the ability: "Noon, Boot: If this dude has 1 or more influence, give Nicodemus a control point, to a maximum of 3." At Nightfall, or if he is ever at home, Nicodemus loses all his control points.

cards.title: Jacqueline Isham
cards.text: When Jacqueline joins a mark's posse, or a posse opposing a job, she becomes a stud until the end of the shootout.
cards.flavor: "Sir, I already told you: I'm not looking for a fight, but I'm more than ready to defend what's ours. Last Warning."

cards.title: The Joker's Smile
cards.text: Whenever a joker is aced during lowball, the controller gains 1 ghost rock. Controller Noon, Boot: Discard a joker to gain 1 ghost rock and draw a card. Controller Noon, Boot: Pay 1 ghost rock to move a joker from your Boot Hill to your discard pile.

cards.title: The Mayor's Office
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Give +1 or -1 influence to a nearby dude.
cards.flavor: "I know a thing or two about Mayor Star that will help persuade him to support our cause." -Al Swearengen

cards.title: Pony Express
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Discard a card to draw a card.
cards.flavor: "We might be isolated in the middle of the Sioux Nation, but the riders still get through." -Laura Banks

cards.title: 2nd Bank of Gomorra
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Place 2 ghost rock (from the bank) on this deed. Controller Noon, Boot: Take all ghost rock from this deed and add it to your stash.

cards.title: New Town Hall
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Add a permanent control point to this deed. Controller Noon, Boot: Remove all control points from this deed.

cards.title: Pettigrew's Pawnshop
cards.text: After a non-Gadget goods is brought into play, this deed's controller gains 1 ghost rock.
cards.flavor: "Best thing is, they don't ask any questions!" -Baker Andrews

cards.title: Hustings
cards.text: All dudes not controlled by this deed's controller have -1 influence while booted at home.
cards.flavor: "Remember boys: vote early, and vote often." -E.B. Farnum

cards.title: The Orphanage
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: All deeds with 2 or more control points get -1 control points and +2 production until after the next Production phase.
cards.flavor: "Why is there a jackalope in the kitchen?" -Willa Mae MacGowan

cards.title: Yan Li's Tailoring
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Give a dude +1 influence.
cards.flavor: "A good tailor is invaluable. You would not believe the number of times I've had this shirt mended. It still appears impeccable, does it not?" -Alexander Sequoia

cards.title: B & B Attorneys
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Give a wanted dude 1 bounty, or remove 1 bounty from a wanted dude.
cards.flavor: "No matter who comes or goes, there's no shortage of work." -Johnny Brocklehurst

cards.title: Clanton Ranch
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: If you are not the Dealer, gain 1 ghost rock.
cards.flavor: "Lucy, the Earps, Doc, the Cowboys... All lay slain by the wrath of vengeance, and it all leads back to the devil known as Stone." -Padre Ernesto de Diaz

cards.title: Dead Dog Tavern
cards.text: (Control of Rowdy deeds is determined by bullets instead of influence.)
cards.flavor: "Poor attorneys. Turns out more than just a dog died in there. Gotta say, though, I feel a lot worse for the dog. The folks some of these fools defended, it's no wonder they went out like this." -Xiong "Wendy" Cheng

cards.title: Charlie's Place
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Give a dude at this location +2 or -2 bullets.
cards.flavor: "Mr. Landers stopped by, said he spotted Wendy and Lucy on their travels." -Genesee "Gina" Tailfeathers

cards.title: Long Strides Ranch
cards.text: While you control at least two Horses, this deed gets +2 production. Controller Noon, Boot: Attach a Horse from your hand to your dude, reducing its cost by 2 (a Gadget still needs to be invented.)
cards.flavor: "Keep Diego's feed away from my herds. It ain't normal." -Jon Longstride

cards.title: Shane & Graves Security
cards.text: Controller Shootout, Boot: A 2-stud Gunslinger token joins your posse at a nearby deed.
cards.flavor: "Graves' name is never leaving our business. It's the least I can do in his memory." -Nathan Shane

cards.title: Killer Bunnies Casino
cards.text: The controller of this deed may discard one additional card each Nightfall.
cards.flavor: "I sure do miss Clementine and her bar. Here's hoping I can find an establishment with equal beauties in Lost Angels." -Pancho Castillo

cards.title: Mount Moriah Cemetery
cards.text: Spells played at this location have their cost reduced by 1 (minimum zero)
cards.flavor: "How can townsfolk be so blind? The land itself is rejecting them. It even refuses to hold their dead." -Sifting Squirrel

cards.title: Nickel Night Inn
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Boot a dude with a value of 3 or less at a nearby location.
cards.flavor: "The drinks are as hard as the beds, probably to help you forget about where it is you're staying." -Forster Cooke

cards.title: Cattle Market
cards.text:
If another Ranch is in play, this deed gets +1 control points.
Dudes at this deed get +3 value.
cards.flavor: "I'll say one thing for Tombstone: at least I felt safe eating steak again." -Xiong "Wendy" Cheng

cards.title: Hunter Protections
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Boot your dude without a control point at this location. Raise their bounty by 2. They get 1 permanent control point.
cards.flavor: "Sloane left town, but they're still in business. Bloody suspicious." -Clyde Owens

cards.title: Sherman Mortgage
cards.text:
When a shootout starts, boot this deed.
While unbooted, increase the cost of each other player's deeds by 1 for every four deeds that player owns (round down).

cards.title: Circle M Ranch
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: If you have 3 or fewer cards in your hand, draw a card.
cards.flavor: "If it weren't for the Morgan Cattle Company, Gomorra would have surely become a ghost town by now." -Irving Patterson

cards.title: The Gomorra Gazette
cards.text: Controller React, Boot: After an opposing dude's bounty increases, gain ghost rock equal to their influence.
cards.flavor: "Sheriff Burnett's crime-predicting algorithms mean I can get tomorrow's headlines today!" -Andrea McCormick

cards.title: Pat's Perch
cards.flavor: "Rafi hid out here while he learned to deal with his new way of life. Or unlife, guess I should say. Place still has a strange aura around it, I'd be careful putting in a claim." -Nathan Shane

cards.title: Epidemic Laboratory
cards.text: Controller Noon Job, Boot: Mark this deed. Your leader must have at least one skill. If successful, this deed permanently gains +1 control points and +1 production.

cards.title: Old Marge's Manor
cards.text: During shootouts, the controller can use ghost rock on this deed to pay for action cards and Gadget abilities. Controller React, Boot: Before making a play, move all ghost rock (not bounty) from a card you control to this deed. Controller Noon, Boot: Place 1 ghost rock on this deed.

cards.title: Surveyor's Office
cards.text: This deed is adjacent to all Out of Town Deeds. Controller Noon, Boot: Move your dude from this location to an adjacent location.

cards.title: Baird's Build & Loan
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Play a deed, reducing its cost by 2.
cards.flavor: "Just ask Mr. Healey, you don't want be in Baird's debt. There's something off about that man." -Larry "Sevens" Swift

cards.title: Carter's Bounties
cards.text: Controller Shootout, Boot: Your dude joins your posse (from any location).
cards.flavor: "I'm sorry, but it definitely said you had to bring them in alive and breathing. Harrowed ain't quite that." -Carter Richardson

cards.title: Walters Creek Distillery
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Boot a Saloon or Casino that you own or control on this street. If you booted a Casino, gain 2 ghost rock. If you booted a Saloon, you may discard a card to draw a card.

cards.title: California Tax Office
cards.text: This deed enters play booted. Controller Noon, Boot: Target another player's dude. That dude's owner either pays their upkeep or discards them. Reduce their upkeep to 0 until after the next Upkeep.

cards.title: Hellstromme Plant #9
cards.text: Controller Noon/Shootout, Pay 1 Ghost Rock, boot: Target a dude you own and control. Unboot the the target's Horse or Gadget, and you may use one of the abilities on that attachment an additional time this turn.

cards.title: Huntsmen's Society
cards.text: The controller's dudes at nearby locations with a value of 10 or higher get -1 upkeep.
cards.flavor: "Abominations are all over the west. Trick is to get folks to gear up and treat it as more than a hunting opportunity." -Lacy O'Malley

cards.title: Cliff's #4 Saloon
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Your dude at a nearby location you control becomes a stud.
cards.flavor: "When the plague hit, some folks thought a bottle from Cliff's would surely cure them. Fools." -Erik Samson

cards.title: General Store
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Attach a goods or spell, reducing the cost by 2.
cards.flavor: "We've got everything you need! As long as what you need is guns and tinned beans."

cards.title: Silent Sigil
cards.text: The number of cards you can discard during Nightfall is reduced by one. Controller React: After you refill your hand during Nightfall, draw a card.

cards.title: "Open Wound"
cards.text: This deed is adjacent to all other Open Wounds. Controller Noon Repeat: Pay 1 ghost rock to move one of your dudes from this location to an adjacent location.
cards.flavor: "Even the land will bleed sometimes." -Lydia Bear-Hands

cards.title: Railroad Station
cards.text: Controller Noon, Boot: Move your dude from this location to another location (without booting).
cards.flavor: "Baird took over running the station after Ivor fell. I'm done being his delivery boy." -Lane Healey

cards.title: The Whateley Estate
cards.text: Owner React, Boot: After a dude moves to this location, boot them. Controller Noon, Boot: Put a non-dude card from your Boot Hill into your discard pile.
cards.flavor: "The Caretaker is maintaining it until I return." -Nicodemus Whateley

cards.title: Baijiu Jar
cards.text: While at a Saloon, this dude gets +3 value and +1 influence. Shootout, Boot: Discard three cards to draw four cards.
cards.flavor: "The amount of that stuff Mr. Outang knocks back would kill a man." -Stevie Lyndon

cards.title: Pair of Six-Shooters
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution, Boot: Change the suit and value of a card in your draw hand.
cards.flavor: "I kept them after Katie left town. Honored if you had them." -Austin Stoker

cards.title: La Quema
cards.text: This dude gets +3 Value. Shootout, Boot: This dude joins your posse (moving if necessary). You may boot an opposing dude.
cards.flavor: "Rumors say one day El Grajo will return." -Jacqueline Isham

cards.title: Bluetick
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Move this dude to the location of a wanted dude.
cards.flavor: "This hound's nose for crime is even more impressive than mine!" -Clyde Owens

cards.title: Hawley's Rose
cards.text:
This dude gains the Abomination keyword.
During Sundown, this dude gets +1 influence and an additional +1 influence if there's an opposing dude at this deed.

cards.title: Peacemaker
cards.text: This dude cannot be changed to a draw. This dude cannot have their bullets lowered by another players' Shootout ability.
cards.flavor: "Gets a lot more peaceful once you've pistol whipped all the troublemakers." -"Thunder Boy" Nabbe

cards.title: Bowie Knife
cards.text: You may attach this card to your dude in a posse (paying all costs) as a Shootout play (even to a booted dude, or at a location you don't control.) This dude is a stud. If there is an unbooted non-Melee Weapon in the opposing posse, Bowie Knife provides no bullet bonus and does not make this dude a stud.

cards.title: Culpability Scientizer
cards.text: After this is invented, give a dude 2 bounty. Noon: Discard this card to call out a wanted dude at this location. If this results in a shootout, make a shootout play before the Dealer makes the first play.

cards.title: Shotgun
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: Ace an opposing dude with value lower than this dude's bullet rating.
cards.flavor: "Messy, sure. But it gets the job done." -Xiong "Wendy" Cheng

cards.title: Disingenuine Currency Press
cards.text:
After this Gadget is invented, gain 4 ghost rock.
When this Gadget is discarded from play, its owner draws a card.
cards.flavor: "Running a business is easy. Why don't more people just print their own money?" -Tallulah "Lula" Morgan

cards.title: Faithful Hound
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: Target a goods in the opposing posse. Pull. If the pull is lower than the value of the goods, boot it. You may discard Faithful Hound to discard the goods instead.

cards.title: Tusk
cards.text:
After this card enters play, draw a card.
This dude gets +5 value for the purpose of opposing card effects.
cards.flavor: "Not a classier tool out there for hunting." -Shelby Hunt

cards.title: Mustang
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Move this dude (without booting).
cards.flavor: "If you're ever lost, trust a mustang. He knows the way back." -Jon Longstride

cards.title: Pearl-Handled Revolver
cards.text: This dude is a stud.
cards.flavor: "Flashy gun. You got the skill to go with it?" -Baker Andrews

cards.title: Xemo's Turban
cards.text: Noon Repeat, Boot, Pull: If the pull is not ♣, you may pay 1 ghost rock to draw a card, discard a card, and unboot Xemo's Turban.
cards.flavor: "It didn't save Xemo..." -Rham

cards.title: Roan
cards.text: React, Boot: When joining a posse, this dude does not boot (this does not allow a booted dude to join a posse).
cards.flavor: "Good for a short burst of speed but not for endurance." -Maggie Harris

cards.title: See-Through Spectacles
cards.text: Resolution, Boot: Choose a card in your draw hand. If it is ♥, change its value to a value you do not have in that hand; otherwise, change its suit to ♥. This counts as modifying your hand rank.
cards.flavor: "Well, look at that!"

cards.title: Winchester Model 1873
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: Boot this dude to give them +1 bullets and make them a stud.
cards.flavor: "I'd much rather deal with maze dragons from a distance" -Smiling Frog

cards.title: Hydro-Puncher
cards.text: This dude can attach two Weapons. If this dude is not a Gadget, both Weapons must be Melee. While this dude has two Weapons attached, they are a stud. Shootout, Boot: Boot an opposing dude and one of their attached cards.
cards.flavor: "Now THAT packs a wallop!"

cards.title: LeMat Revolver
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution, Boot: Increase your hand rank by this dude's bullet rating. Resolution, Boot: Only use this ability if this dude is a stud and your shooter. While, by including the top card of your discard pile with your draw hand, you have three pairs (of different values), increase your hand rank by this dude's bullet rating.

cards.title: Pinto
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: This dude joins your posse (without booting, and even if booted).
cards.flavor: "No, no, no, I said PINTO not PEDRO. Did you really think I wanted a steed slower than molasses?" -Vida Azul

cards.title: Flame-Thrower
cards.text: This dude is a stud. Shootout, Pay 1-3 Ghost Rock, Boot: Raise the bullets on this Gadget by 1 for each ghost rock spent. Each round's loser takes 1 extra casualty.

cards.title: Quickdraw Handgun
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution, Boot: If you have a legal draw hand, exchange draw hands with the cheatin' player. Your new hand is considered legal.
cards.flavor: "Don't test me." -Seth Bullock

cards.title: Ragged Mule
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: This dude joins your posse. Pay 1 ghost rock or discard Ragged Mule. Noon, Boot: Move this dude. Pay 1 ghost rock or discard Ragged Mule.

cards.title: Mechanical Horse
cards.text: Noon Repeat, Pay 1 Ghost Rock: Move this dude to an adjacent location. Noon Repeat, Pay 2 Ghost Rock: Move this dude. React, Boot: Prevent this dude from booting when they join a posse (this does not let a booted dude join a posse).

cards.title: Tin Star
cards.text:
This dude gains the Deputy keyword.
Wanted dudes cannot refuse this dude's call-outs.
cards.flavor: "Recite after me Deborah: 'I follow the path of truth and honor. If I ever stray, this badge and God's word will lead me back..." -Abram Grothe

cards.title: Wendy's Teethkickers
cards.text: React, Boot: After another player's dude goes home booted from this location, this dude gets +1 influence until end of the turn. Unboot this dude.
cards.flavor: "Dang! Hope I can buff that out."

cards.title: Jael's Guile
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution, Boot: If your hand is cheatin', you must boot this dude to use this ability. The cheatin' player boots or discards a dude in their posse, then boots or discards a dude in their posse. Wanted dudes must be chosen if possible.

cards.title: Personal Ornithopter
cards.text: Shootout Repeat, Pay 1 Ghost Rock: This dude joins your posse (moving if necessary). Shootout, Boot: Send this dude home booted.
cards.flavor: "I can see my house from here!" -Dr. Delphi Wallis

cards.title: Scoop Hound
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: Shootout plays cannot send dudes home booted (they remain in the posse without booting) or bring dudes into either posse.
cards.flavor: "Hold that pose!" -Alexis Mirges

cards.title: Buffalo Rifle
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: This dude joins a posse at an adjacent location without moving or booting.
cards.flavor: "They won't even see me comin'. Mostly because I don't have to get outta this spot." -Reggie Mallard

cards.title: Rapier
cards.text:
If there is an unbooted non-Melee Weapon in the opposing posse, Rapier provides +0 bullets.
This dude gets +1 value.
cards.flavor: "An elegant tool from a more civilized age." -Alexander Sequoia

cards.title: Yagn's Mechanical Skeleton
cards.text: This dude gains the Gadget keyword. React, Boot: When this dude would be moved or booted by another player's ability, they do not move or boot.
cards.flavor: "Who's Yagn? Who cares, this is great!" - Chuan "Jen" Qi

cards.title: Bio-Charge Neutralizer
cards.text: This dude is a stud. This card cannot be traded, and is not affected by other players' card effects. Noon, Boot, Pull: If the pull is ♣, discard this goods. Otherwise, attach it to another of your dudes at this location.

cards.title: Guide Horse
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Move this dude to town square.
cards.flavor: "Mr. Outang loves this horse. Leads him straight to town, where he can hit up a saloon." -Chuan "Jen" Qi

cards.title: Soul Cage
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution, Boot: Choose an Abomination from your discard pile or Boot Hill with a cost equal to or lower than the cheatin' hand's rank. Put it into play at this location, reducing its cost to zero. If this is a shootout, it joins your posse.

cards.title: Fancy New Hat
cards.text: This dude's influence cannot be reduced by other players' abilities.
cards.flavor: "One per customer now, ya hear?" -Pettigrew

cards.title: Silver-Weaved Staff
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: Boot an opposing spell.
cards.flavor: "The silver apparently deflects harmful energies. I admit, it's less disgusting than most defenses against the magic arts." -Valeria Batten

cards.title: Soul Blast
cards.text: Shootout Hex X, Boot: Target an opposing dude. X is that dude's grit. If successful, send them home booted. If successful by 6 or more, ace them instead. If unsuccessful, boot this Huckster.

cards.title: Corporeal Twist
cards.text: Shootout Hex 4, Boot: Give an opposing dude -1 bullets and -2 value. If that dude is aced or discarded during this shootout, this Huckster gains 1 permanent control point.

cards.title: Phantom Fingers
cards.text: Noon/Shootout Hex 6, Boot: Target an opposing dude's goods in a nearby location (if this is a shootout, it must be in the shootout). Boot it, and it loses all traits, abilities, and bullet bonuses. If it's Mystical or a Gadget, draw a card.

cards.title: Fetch
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution Hex 5, Boot: When you discard your draw hand this round, you may place a card from that draw hand into your play hand. If this is a shootout, reduce your casualties by 3 this round.

cards.title: Paralysis Mark
cards.text: Noon Hex, Boot: Boot a dude with value X at this location.
cards.flavor: "Spectral coils, hold the sacrifice tight. It's feeding time, my children!" -Ursula, the Worm Queen

cards.title: Phantasm
cards.text: Noon Hex 9, Boot: Move an opposing unbooted dude at a nearby location to a location adjacent to them (without booting). Noon Hex 12, Boot: Move another player's booted dude at this location to an adjacent location.

cards.title: Shadow Walk
cards.text: Noon Hex 7, Boot: Move this dude (without booting). Shootout Hex 7, Boot: This dude joins your posse. You may discard this Hex to make another Shootout play.

cards.title: Forget
cards.text: Noon Hex 5, Boot: Target an ability printed on a dude at a nearby location. That ability cannot be used until after Nightfall.
cards.flavor: "It slipped your mind, you say?" -Jonah Essex

cards.title: Blood Curse
cards.text: Noon Hex 9, Boot: A dude at a nearby location gets -1 influence and -1 bullets.
cards.flavor: "A little manipulation goes a long way." -Sylvester Heath

cards.title: Sight Beyond Sight
cards.text: Noon Hex 6, Boot: Look at a random card in an opponent's hand. Noon Hex 9, Boot: Look at two random cards in an opponent's hand. Noon Hex 12, Boot: Look at three random cards in an opponent's hand.

cards.title: Onward Christian Soldiers
cards.text: Shootout Miracle 4, Boot: All dudes in your posse get +1 bullets, and cannot have their bullets reduced or changed to a draw by other players' card effects.
cards.flavor: "I carry onward - for Abram, for Erik, for everyone." -Deborah West

cards.title: Get Behind Me, Satan!
cards.text: Resolution Miracle 5, Boot: Reduce your casualties this round by this dude's Blessed rating. Target opposing Abomination does not contribute to the posse's draw and stud ratings during the next shootout round.

cards.title: Lay On Hands
cards.text: React Miracle 6, Boot: When another dude at a nearby location would be discarded as a casualty or aced at any time, boot this Blessed to send that dude home booted instead. That dude does not unboot during Nightfall this turn.

cards.title: Confession
cards.text: Noon Miracle 5, Boot: Transfer one bounty from a dude at a nearby location to your stash. Noon Miracle 6, Boot: Give a dude at this location one bounty. You may boot this dude to target a dude in an adjacent location instead.

cards.title: Holy Roller
cards.text: Shootout Miracle 6, Boot: This dude gets +1 bullets and cannot be chosen as a casualty this round unless you lose by 3 or more hand ranks.
cards.flavor: "Behold, the power of the Lord!"

cards.title: Shield of Faith
cards.text: Shootout Miracle 7, Boot: Except for Cheatin' Resolutions, player's card effects cannot ace or discard dudes owned by another player. Reduce your casualties this round by 1.

cards.title: Consecration
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution Miracle 7: One of your dudes becomes a stud and gets +2 bullets and +2 influence until Nightfall. If this is a shootout, reduce your casualties this round by 3.

cards.title: Walk The Path
cards.text: Noon Miracle 6, Boot: Move your other dude to this Blessed's location (from any location, without booting.) Shootout Miracle 7, Boot: One of your dudes joins this dude's posse (moving if necessary). Unboot that dude.

cards.title: Soothe
cards.text: Noon Miracle 8, Boot: Boot this dude to unboot another dude at a nearby location.
cards.flavor: "The Lord they God is with thee whithersoever thou goest." -Joshua 1:9

cards.title: Sword of the Spirit
cards.text: Noon Miracle 7: Give a dude +1 bullets. While that dude has a Melee Weapon, they become a stud and cannot be affected by opposing spells.
cards.flavor: "I beseech you, Lord: protect her."

cards.title: Sun-Touched Raven
cards.text: Shootout Spirit 6, Boot: Look at the top five cards of your deck. You may discard up to three of them. You may boot this Shaman to draw a card.
cards.flavor: "Guidance comes in many forms."

cards.title: Strength of the Ancestors
cards.text: Noon Spirit 5, Boot: This dude gets +3 bullets, becomes a stud, and other players' card effects cannot boot them or send them home booted. These effects end if this dude leaves this location (or at the end of the turn.)

cards.title: Mother Bear's Rage
cards.text: Noon Spirit 5, Boot: A 2-stud Gunslinger enters play at this location or an adjacent deed and calls out a dude.
cards.flavor: "Woe betide those who violate the Treaty and our lands." -Eagle Woman

cards.title: Owl's Insight
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution Spirit 5, Boot: Attach any number of goods or spells from your play hand, reducing the cost of each by 1. Draw cards until your play hand is at its maximum size. If this is a shootout, reduce your casualties by 2 this round.

cards.title: Spirit Dance
cards.text: Shootout Spirit 10, Boot: A 2-stud Gunslinger token enters play and joins your posse.
cards.flavor: "Our power is much stronger in the Black Hills. The spirits we call even take the shapes of men." -Black Elk

cards.title: Red Horse's Tail
cards.text: Noon Spirit X, Boot: X is the value of a dude at this location. Boot that dude. Shootout Spirit X, Boot: X is the grit of an opposing dude. Send that dude home booted.

cards.title: Spirit Trail
cards.text: This location is adjacent to each other location that has a Spirit Trail attached. Noon Spirit 6, Boot: Move your dude from this location (without booting, and even if booted).

cards.title: Many Speak As One
cards.text: Noon Spirit 9, Boot: Put a 0-draw, 1-influence Ancestor Spirit token into play at this location.
cards.flavor: "All of the tribes and their ancestors will join as one to guide us." -Eagle Woman

cards.title: Ghostly Communion
cards.text: Your outfit is considered a Holy Ground while casting this spell. Noon Spirit 5, Boot: Move this dude to a Holy Ground or a location adjacent to one. Shootout Spirit 7, Boot: This dude joins your posse at a Holy Ground or a location adjacent to one. This dude becomes a stud.

cards.title: Fire of Nanahbozho
cards.text: Can only attach to a deed. This deed gains Holy Ground. Shamans get +2 Shaman while at a deed with one or more of this Totem. Noon/Shootout Spirit 10, Boot: Unboot a dude at a nearby deed. If that dude is at this deed, make another play.

cards.title: Establishin' Who's in Charge
cards.text: Noon Job: Mark an in-town deed. If successful, give the deed 1 permanent control point.
cards.flavor: "You might have a little piece of paper from the Sioux that says you can mine here, but my friends with the guns here say this claim belongs to us." - Frank Bryant

cards.title: Make 'Em Sweat
cards.text: Shootout: Boot your dude to reduce another dude's bullet rating by your dude's bullet rating. If their bullet rating is 0 (or less), boot them.
cards.flavor: "Cross the law here, you'll have me to reckon with." - Seth Bullock

cards.title: Polite Inquiries
cards.text: Noon: Boot your dude at a location other than home. Draw cards up to your dude's bullet rating (maximum 4), then discard the same number of cards. Draw a card.
cards.flavor: "I'd hate to hear that you came by any misfortune." - Al Swearengen

cards.title: Bottom Dealin'
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution: Discard the cheatin' player's draw hand and replace it with the top five cards of your deck (those cards still go to your discard pile).
cards.flavor: "They never see it comin'." - Zeb Whateley-Dupont

cards.title: Make the Smart Choice
cards.text: Shootout: Reduce a dude's bullets by their influence. That dude's controller may send them home booted (even if already booted).
cards.flavor: "It would be for the best if you just sold up and left town." - E.B. Farnum

cards.title: Mugging
cards.text: Noon Job: Mark an opposing dude. Boot up to two cards attached to the mark. If the job is successful, send the mark home booted, and you may ace up to two booted cards attached to the mark.

cards.title: Zhu's Ferocity
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: This dude gets +1 bullets and +1 value, and an opposing dude gets -1 bullets. Combo if this dude has higher bullets than the opposing dude.

cards.title: ...It's Who You Know
cards.text: Noon: One of your dudes calls out an opposing dude at their location. If accepted, your dude becomes a stud for this shootout. When forming shootout hands this shootout, all dudes use their influence instead of bullets to determine how many cards each player draws (but keep their bullet type).

cards.title: Raking Dragons
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: Boot a dude and give them -2 value. Combo if that dude has lower value than this dude.
cards.flavor: "A rake with more than 9 teeth." - Yunxu Jiang

cards.title: The Stakes Just Rose
cards.text: Shootout: One of your dudes joins your posse and becomes a stud.
cards.flavor: "Your associates didn't stop meddling in my business, Farnum, so I've brought in some help." - Huang Li

cards.title: Sun in Yer Eyes
cards.text: Shootout: Target dude in this shootout gets -2 bullets or becomes a draw. You may spend 1 ghost rock to give both effects to that dude.
cards.flavor: "High noon? Too cliche. I do my killing before breakfast. Easier on the stomach." - El Anónimo

cards.title: Ambush
cards.text: Noon Job, Boot: Mark a dude. If the mark is not wanted, raise the bounty on each dude in your posse by 1. If successful, ace the mark.
cards.flavor: "We'll pretend to be simple prospectors to get the jump on these ghosts." - Hao-T'e Zui

cards.title: Belligerence
cards.text: Noon: Give a wanted dude +1 bullets and +1 influence until Noon next turn. Noon, Pay 1 Ghost Rock: Give a dude 1 bounty to unboot them.
cards.flavor: "Come at me, mutton-puncher!"

cards.title: Coachwhip!
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution: The cheatin' player boots one of their dudes. If this is a shootout, the dude is aced instead. If your hand is legal, you choose the target instead.
cards.flavor: "Beware of snakes in the grass. They might be the kind that bite." - Avie Cline

cards.title: Rabbit's Lunar Leap
cards.keywords: Technique • Tao of the Jade Rabbit
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: This dude joins your posse. You may unboot this dude. Combo if there are more dudes in the opposing posse.
cards.flavor: "The cow jumped over the moon? What nonsense! Me, on the other hand..." - Xui Yin Chen

cards.title: Hiding in the Shadows
cards.text: Noon: Target one of your dudes. Other players cannot target or affect that dude with Shootout abilities.
cards.flavor: "It may not be the most glamorous tactic, but it sure beats getting shot." - Agent John "Aces! Radcliffe

cards.title: Ol' Fashioned Hangin'
cards.text: Noon Job: Mark an opposing dude with at least 2 bounty. If successful, ace the mark, and your leader (if still in play) gets 1 permanent control point.
cards.flavor: "Maybe the law ain't perfect, but it's the only one we got. Without it, we got nothin'." - Bass Reeves

cards.title: Pistol Whip
cards.text: Shootout: Boot your dude in this posse to send a dude in the other posse home booted. Your dude gets -1 bullets (minimum 0).
cards.flavor: "Go on, say 'soon' again, I dare ya!" - Allie Hensman

cards.title: Rabbit's Deception
cards.keywords: Technique • Tao of the Jade Rabbit
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: Send this dude home booted. If they were unbooted when you played this card, you may also send an opposing dude home booted. Combo if there is a stud in the opposing posse.
cards.flavor: "Try to keep up!" - Hao-T'e Zui

cards.title: Calling the Cavalry
cards.text: Shootout: During this round's resolution, the player with the most Horses in their posse gains +1 hand rank. One dude in your posse becomes a stud until the end of the shootout.

cards.title: Faster on the Draw
cards.text: Shootout: Give your dude +1 bullets. If they are a Deputy, they become a stud. Give one opposing dude - 2 bullets.
cards.flavor: "Having a badge is helpful, but at the end of the day, it matters just as much that you get the drop on'em." - Bass Reeves

cards.title: Great Sage Matching Heaven
cards.keywords: Technique • Tao of Bull Demon King
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: This dude gets +1 Influence and gains the Harrowed keyword. Combo if the other posse has less influence than your posse.

cards.title: Technological Exhibition
cards.text: Noon Job: Mark an in-town location. Your leader must have Mad Scientist. If successful, your leader invents a Gadget in your hand or discard pile without booting, reducing its cost and difficulty by 5. If you marked the town square, give the Gadget +1 control points permanently.

cards.title: Comin' Up Roses
cards.text: Resolution: Choose a card in your draw hand with no duplicate value in that hand. Change the card to the suit of your choice. Cheatin' Resolution: Change one or two cards in your draw hand to the suit and value of your choice. Their new values cannot match another value in that hand. For the rest of the shootout, while your hand contains a legal flush or straight, you have +2 hand rank.

cards.title: Kidnappin'
cards.text: Noon Job, Boot: Mark an opposing dude. Your posse must have more total bullets than the marked dude. Give 1 bounty to each dude that joins your posse during the job. If successful, discard the mark.
cards.flavor: "Let's go for a ride." - Landon Grimes

cards.title: Pinned Down
cards.text: Shootout: Target dude must be selected as the first casualty. If they are chosen as a shooter, they get -3 bullets.
cards.flavor: "Anybody want to lend a hand? Sniper's got a bead on me!" - Enrique Dos Santos

cards.title: Two Hundred Fifty Rounds
cards.keywords: Technique • Tao of Bull Demon King
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: Reduce your casualties this round by one. Combo if you control this location.
cards.flavor: "It's cute that you're trying."

cards.title: Bounty Hunter
cards.text: Noon: A 2-stud Gunslinger token enters play at a wanted dude's location and calls out that dude, who cannot refuse.
cards.flavor: "No need to struggle now, hear? You're just gonna make it more painful for yourself." - El Anónimo

cards.title: Ridden Down
cards.text: Noon: Boot your horse to send a dude without a Horse at that location home booted.
cards.flavor: "It's more fun this way. Ride, boys!" - Lane Healey

cards.title: This'll Hurt in the Morning'
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution: Discard one or two cards of your choice in an opponent's cheatin' hand. Replace them with cards drawn from their owner's deck. If your hand is legal, then for each card discarded, your opponent must either pay you 1 ghost rock or ace the card.

cards.title: Rabbit's Sweeping Snare
cards.keywords: Technique • Tao of the Jade Rabbit
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: Mark an opposing dude. That dude becomes a draw. If your posse has fewer dudes than the opposing posse, boot up to two cards attached to that dude.
cards.flavor: "So slow and clumsy! I could beat all of you single-handed." - Xui Yin Chen

cards.title: Ricochet
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution: The cheating player discards their shooter. If your hand is legal, you do not take casualties this round and draw a card.
cards.flavor: "Bullets are hardly a threat when pitted against turtle's protection." - Black Elk

cards.title: Shortcut
cards.text: Noon: Move your unbooted dude to another location. React: When forming a posse at an adjacent location, target dude does not boot to move to the shootout's location.
cards.flavor: "I know this town inside and out."

cards.title: Trick Shooting
cards.text: Shootout: Give your dude +1 bullets. Pull. If the pull is red, look at a number of cards from the top of your deck equal to your dude's bullet rating and put one of them into your hand.
cards.flavor: "Pick a card, then toss it high in the air for me." - "Thunder Boy" Nabbe

cards.title: Crushing Inevitability
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique, Boot: Target an opposing dude. If that dude is booted, they do not contribute to draw hands this round. If the target has a lower value than this dude, then they must be selected as the first casualty this round.

cards.title: Recruitment Drive
cards.text: Noon Job: Mark the town square. If successful, put a dude or deed into play from your discard pile, reducing its cost by 5 ghost rock.
cards.flavor: "We're looking for good people to help maintain order and mend relations here." - Eagle Woman

cards.title: Too Much Attention
cards.text: Noon: Boot a wanted dude. Noon: Boot a card worth one or more control points.
cards.flavor: "Which part o'target folks that people won't miss' did you not understand, Grimes?" - Ursula, the Worm Queen

cards.title: Unprepared
cards.text: Shootout: Boot a dude and give them -1 bullets. They cannot use their abilities. Shootout: Boot up to 2 cards attached to a dude. Those cards lose all traits, abilities, and bullet bonuses.

cards.title: Flight of the Lepus
cards.text: Cheatin' Resolution: Target up to two dudes controlled by you or the cheatin' player. If you revealed a legal hand, you may target one additional dude. Move those dudes home. If this is as shootout, you may boot them.

cards.title: Meet the New Boss
cards.text: Noon Job: Mark the town square. If successful, your leader gains 1 permanent control point. You may ace this card to give your successful leader a permanent +1 influence.
cards.flavor: "Time to remind the town of all the good I've done for them." - E.B.Farnum

cards.title: Outgunned
cards.text: Resolution: If your posse has higher total bullets than the opposing posse, boot your shooter to increase your hand rank by 2.
cards.flavor: "We're going to need better gunmen if we're going to stand up for the workers here." - Randall

cards.title: It's Not What You Know...
cards.text: Resolution: Lower a player's hand rank by 1. Cheatin' Resolution: Lower a player's hand rank by 4.
cards.flavor: "I'm sorry madame, would you mind explaining the rules of this game to me again?" - Pancho Castillo

cards.title: No Turning Back
cards.text: Noon: Ace a dude you own and control to gain ghost rock equal to their cost. Resolution: Ace a dude you own and control to reduce your casualties this round to zero. Target dude gets +2 bullets and becomes a stud until the end of the shootout. Your dudes cannot flee this round.
cards.flavor: "I knew it was a fight for our lives." - Wyatt Earp

cards.title: Thirst for Blood
cards.text: Shootout: Target your dude with 1 or more influence. That dude becomes a stud or gains +2 bullets; you may increase their bounty by 1 to gain both bonuses instead. Reduce that dude's influence by 1 until after Sundown.

cards.title: Election Day Slaughter
cards.text: Noon Job, Boot: Mark the town square. Each other player may unboot a dude in town. If successful, each other player must ace one of their dudes in town.
cards.flavor: "The bloodshed that day was more than regrettable. Please let me escape my past." - Jessica Patchett

cards.title: Nightmare at Noon
cards.text: Shootout: Give each dude in one posse -1 bullets. Each dude in the shootout with 0 or 1 bullets becomes draw.
cards.flavor: "Not enough bullets to go around." - Xiong "Wendy" Cheng

cards.title: Point Blank
cards.text: Resolution: Boot your non-token stud dude in this posse. Your opponent must ace a dude in their posse with lower bullets than your dude's bullets.
cards.flavor: "At this range? With this gadget? Don't worry, even if I miss, I won't miss." - Adelaide Rose

cards.title: Joker (black)
cards.text:
This card is only used for draw hands and pulls.

You choose its suit and value. Ace the joker after use.

cards.title: Joker (red)
cards.text:
This card is only used for draw hands and pulls.

You choose its suit and value. Ace the joker after use.

cards.title: Ancestor Spirit
cards.text: Cannot be included in decks. Remove this token from the game if it leaves this location, or at the end of the turn.

cards.title: Gunslinger
cards.text: Cannot be included in decks. Remove this token from the game after this shootout.
cards.flavor: "I can be hired to do anything in this world someone needs done, except make a decision for 'em." - El Anónimo
